# 🧠 BraTS – Brain Tumor Segmentation Dataset

## 📌 Dataset Overview

- **Full Name:** Brain Tumor Segmentation (BraTS) Challenge Dataset  
- **Organizer:** MICCAI BraTS Challenge  
- **Official Website:** https://braintumorsegmentation.org/  
- **Primary Domain:** Brain Glioma MRI  
- **Access Type:** Public (Registration Required)  
- **Data Format:** NIfTI (.nii / .nii.gz)

---

## 🧠 Description

The BraTS (Brain Tumor Segmentation) dataset is a multi-institutional collection of pre-operative brain MRI scans of glioma patients. It is one of the most widely used benchmark datasets for automated brain tumor segmentation research.

The dataset includes expert-annotated tumor segmentation masks and is curated for standardized evaluation of machine learning and deep learning models.

BraTS is officially used in the MICCAI Brain Tumor Segmentation Challenge and is considered a gold-standard dataset for brain tumor analysis.

---

## 📡 MRI Modalities Included

Each patient case contains four aligned MRI sequences:

| Modality | Description |
|----------|------------|
| T1 | Native T1-weighted MRI |
| T1c | T1-weighted MRI with contrast enhancement |
| T2 | T2-weighted MRI |
| FLAIR | Fluid Attenuated Inversion Recovery |

All modalities are co-registered, skull-stripped, and resampled to uniform spacing.

---

## 🧩 Segmentation Labels

Tumor annotations are provided with the following labels:

| Label Value | Region |
|------------|--------|
| 0 | Background |
| 1 | Necrotic and Non-Enhancing Tumor Core |
| 2 | Edema |
| 4 | Enhancing Tumor |

### Derived Evaluation Regions

- **Whole Tumor (WT)** = 1 + 2 + 4  
- **Tumor Core (TC)** = 1 + 4  
- **Enhancing Tumor (ET)** = 4  

